    "rationale": "<p>Choice B is correct. It's given that the base area of the right rectangular prism is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"24 t c m squared\"><mn>24</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi>cm</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp;and the length of the base is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"eight thirds c m\"><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>. Dividing the base area by the length yields the width: <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"StartFraction 24 t Over eight thirds EndFraction\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>24</mn><mi>t</mi></mrow><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mfrac></math>, or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"left parenthesis 24 t right parenthesis left parenthesis three eighths right parenthesis\"><mo>(</mo><mn>24</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math>, or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"9 t c m\"><mn>9</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>. It's also given that the height of the prism is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"15 cm\"><mn>15</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mtext>cm</mtext></math>. A right rectangular prism has two rectangular bases and four rectangular lateral faces. The total area of the two bases is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"2 left parenthesis 24 t right parenthesis\"><mn>2</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>24</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo></math>, or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"48 t c m squared\"><mn>48</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi>cm</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>. The four lateral faces include two with dimensions <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"eight thirds c m\"><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>&nbsp;by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"15 cm\"><mn>15</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mtext>cm</mtext></math>&nbsp;and two with dimensions <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"9 t c m\"><mn>9</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>&nbsp;by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"15 c m\"><mn>15</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>. The total area of these four lateral faces is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"2 left parenthesis eight thirds right parenthesis left parenthesis 15 right parenthesis plus 2 left parenthesis 9 t right parenthesis left parenthesis 15 right parenthesis c m squared\"><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>(</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>9</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi>cm</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, which is equivalent to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"80 plus 270 t c m squared\"><mn>80</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>270</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi>cm</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>. Adding this to the total area of the two bases yields <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"48 t plus 270 t plus 80\"><mn>48</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>270</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>80</mn></math>, or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"318 t plus 80 c m squared\"><mn>318</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>80</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi>cm</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>. Thus, the expression, which represents the surface area, in&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"c m squared\"><msup><mi>cm</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, of the right rectangular prism is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"318 t plus 80\"><mn>318</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>80</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>Choice A is incorrect&nbsp;and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.</p>\n<p>Choice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.</p>\n<p>Choice D is incorrect. This is the volume, in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"c m cubed\"><msup><mi>cm</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></math>, not the surface area, in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"c m squared\"><msup><mi>cm</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>.</p>",
